On one hand, it’s well written, towards the middle especially, and the character interactions are fun since it seems like there’s a lot more to the story than we see. On the other hand… there isn’t more to the story. It’s a one shot with half a dozen meaningless callbacks to events that don’t exist in the archive. Which really sucks because in just four thousand words you were able to slot in so many interesting sounding references without making the one shot feel bloated. It has great potential to become a series by exploring things like how everyone knows each other, Iroha’s past, how Anon and Suisei started dating and how they broke up, Koyori’s research or whatever happened at the strip club. I want to like it for what it is whole thing feels like wasted potential.
